Nova Scotia Power’s greatest source of energy is our people. In a culture focused on safety, we’re committed to providing exceptional service to our customers and rewarding jobs to our employees. We’re hiring solution-minded people excited to help us grow into the future. We are currently seeking a 
Technical Business Systems Analyst 
to join our ERP Application Support Team in a full-time permanent position.



Accountabilities



Under the direction of the Manager, ERP IT Systems, the Intermediate Technical Business Systems Analyst is accountable for supporting, maintaining, and evolving enterprise level computer systems to meet established customer service levels and maintain IT Operations best practices.



Responsibilities



The position is responsible for day to day application support of our Oracle Business Intelligence application including the ability to

The Intermediate Technical Business Systems Analyst needs to have the technical ability to support our ERP applications and bring an understanding of application related business processes.


 Troubleshoot and resolve application incidents following standard Incident Management procedures; 

 Assess, prioritize, and complete application requests in a timely and quality manner following standard Request Management procedures; 

 Manage application support issues, requests, and associated customer communications proactively to completion using standard tracking tools; 

 Manage and execute application changes using standard Change Management methodologies; 

 Perform proactive application error and health monitoring; 

 Support and enforce corporate application security policies and procedures; 

 Perform audit controls and reporting related to application access and usage; 

 Effectively self–manage and re-prioritize work to balance resolution of incidents, request fulfillment, and project work to ensure highest priority issues are addressed and deadlines are met; 

 Interact with vendors to resolve application incidents and problems, and research information; 

 Work collaboratively and maintain relationships with business partners, system users, peers, and vendors; 

 Satisfy customer reporting requests through customer education of system functionality or development and execution of reporting, as appropriate; 

 Answer customer questions regarding application usage; 

 Provide after-hours support by participating in an on-call rotation with the ERP technical support team; 

 Complete application system administration requests in a timely and quality manner; 

 Recognize and identify potential areas where existing business policies and procedures require change, or where new ones need to be developed, and make recommendations; 

 Ensure effective use of application security and controls by communicating application policies, procedures, and practices to the application users. 

 Translating business, stakeholder/user requirements to technical specifications. 

 Designing, building and deploying OBIEE Dashboards and reports which includes development, execution of database queries and analysis creation. 

 Participating in data warehouse design for all requests or projects in the BI team and provide business inputs on the source systems (EBS, PeopleSoft, PowerPlan) 

 Developing and updating technical and deployment documentation. 

 Developing Unit tests, validating and troubleshooting in all environments and coordinating the UAT testing for Standard changes. 

 Troubleshooting any data issues by capturing physical queries and analysing the root cause in the areas of Dashboard Reports, Repository, ETL and analyzing the source database systems. 

 End-to-end understanding of the BI application user roles and security controls including all license information. 


You will be responsible for your personal safety and that of co-workers by observing all Occupational Health and Safety Rules and Regulations.



Skills, Capabilities And Experience



The successful candidate will have a University degree or diploma in a computer related discipline and a minimum of two (2) years’ experience in technical client facing support roles with Oracle ERP Systems. An understanding and experience utilizing best practice information technology incident and request management processes is essential.



The Ideal Candidate Will Have




 Sound Oracle Business Intelligence support experience 

 Understanding of ERP Applications/Solutions like Peoplesoft and EBS 

 Strong SQL skills; 

 ETL Development 

 Solid analytical and problem-solving skills; 

 Strong report development skills – specifically the ability to effectively confirm requirements, understand data models and build accurate and effective queries and reports; 

 Excellent interpersonal and communications skills: the ability to communicate with end users to determine details of issues being experienced, and to clearly define request requirements; 

 Ability to understand and bring experience utilizing information technology incident and request management processes and systems. 




The Following Would Be An Asset




 ITIL Foundations training; 

 Experience performing proactive IT audit controls; 

 Working knowledge and experience with access security and controls; 

 Experience satisfying internal and external audit requests for information and evidence; 

 Understanding of accounting and financial concepts in relation to business processes; 

 Experience with PowerPlan, GitHub and Tableau. 



 Reports to 
 : Manager, ERP IT Systems


 Form of Application: 
 Click the APPLY button at the end of the online job posting. Complete all required information fields, and copy and paste your covering letter and resume into the online form.


 Salary: 
 To commensurate with qualifications and experience.


 Must Be Received By: 
 All interested candidates should apply no later than
 March 22 nd 2022. 


Late applications may not receive consideration.


 Recruitment and Promotion Policy: 
 When filling vacant positions, we are determined to hire the best candidates available. We are committed to providing employees with a fair and equal opportunity to compete for jobs. Hiring and promotion of employees is based on skills, capabilities, knowledge and demonstrated abilities.

In accordance with Emera’s occupational health and safety program and the Emera Vaccine Program, subject to any approved accommodation, all employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. For clarity, “fully vaccinated” means 14 days since having the number of doses or combination of doses of a vaccine approved by Health Canada or local public health agencies in the jurisdiction in which they will be employed.

At Emera we value diversity, equity, and inclusion. We strongly encourage applications from all qualified candidates, including persons who identify as racially visible, Indigenous, persons with disabilities, women in underrepresented roles and members of the LGBTQ+ community. Applicants from these equity groups may self-identify through the on-line application process. Emera supports candidates and employees with access and accommodation needs.

If you are selected for an interview and require a specific accommodation, please advise our Talent Acquisition team and we will support you with the recruitment process.

